        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Enable all power rails associated with a specific profile. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Iterates through the list of rails defined for the given profile and instructs the Rail Controller to turn them ON.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">profiles</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The power profiles service instance. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">profile</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The target profile to enable (e.g., POWER_PROFILE_NOMINAL).</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>POWER_PROFILE_SUCCESS</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Operation successful. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>POWER_PROFILE_ERROR_INVALID_PROFILE</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The provided profile ID does not exist. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
